# Surface Critic

**Purpose:** Single source of truth for the surface fix and AI tell check. Called from apply-context tasks (fix new/changed text before writing to .tex) and proposal-context tasks (fix proposed revision before writing to notes file).

---

## Authority

Rules are defined in `../../../references/writing_quality_standards.md` Section III (Surface Fix Rules) and Section IV (AI Tell Pattern Reference, Parts A and B). Read those sections now. The standards file is authoritative.

**Quick reference (non-exhaustive — Section III–IV governs):**
- Em-dash removal: restructure sentence (period, comma, or subordinate clause)
- Artificial colon removal: convert to direct statement
- Transition opener removal: delete sentence-initial Moreover, Furthermore, Additionally, In contrast, Notably, Importantly
- Hedging discipline: at most one hedge per claim; cut non-load-bearing hedges
- Demonstrative discipline: bare this/these/that/those → add noun referent
- AI vocabulary: replace leverage, robust, nuanced, pivotal, crucial, highlight, underscore, etc. with plain alternatives
- Smarmy reframing: "It's not X, it's Y" and variants → direct statement
- Sentence length: any sentence exceeding ~40 words → split
- Paragraph length: any paragraph exceeding ~200 words / ~10 sentences → split

---

## Procedure

### What to scan

**Apply context** (task_edit, rewrite, apply_marked): every sentence in the new or changed text being written to the file. Do NOT scan unchanged surrounding text.

**Proposal context** (ai_detection, word_choice, writing_quality): every sentence in the Proposed Revision before writing it to the notes file. The proposed revision cannot introduce the same class of errors it claims to fix.

### How to check

Work through Section III rules and Section IV Parts A and B systematically, sentence by sentence.

### When a violation is found

Fix it in-place. Restructure, substitute, or split as the rule specifies. Do not flag-and-skip.

### Reporting (apply context only)

If any fixes were made, log them in the change summary: "Surface fix: [what] in sentence [N]."
If no violations found, no entry needed.

### Sentence rhythm (apply context, multi-sentence output only)

After fixing violations, confirm sentence lengths vary. If every new sentence is the same length, vary one or two.

---

## Scope limit

This critic covers surface rules only (Sections III–IV Parts A–B). Argument quality — results-first openings, missing causal mechanism, inventory-style numbers, claims overshooting evidence (Part C) — belongs to the writing_quality task.
